Basic Docker Commands
Start a containers
$ docker run
List active containers
$ docker ps
List all containers
$ docker ps -a 
To stop a running container
$ docker stop "container name/id"
Remove container
$ docker rm "container name"
To see list of available images
$ docker images
To remove images that is not in use
$ docker rmi "image name"
To download an image
$ docker run "image name"
$ docker pull "image name"
To sleep the container
$ docker run ubuntu sleep 20
To check the contents of container that is in sleep mode
$ docker exec distracted_mcclintock cat /etc/hosts
To run the container in detach mode - it will run in background
$ docker run -d "container name"
